def: Pertaining to, derived from, or containing, pentyl; as,pentylic alcohol

A saddle for women, in which the rider sits with both feet onone side of the animal mounted. Sidesaddle flower (Bot.), a plantwith hollow leaves and curiously shaped flowers; -- called alsohuntsman's cup. See Sarracenia.
A leafy shelter; a place covered with foliage. [Obs.]Behind the mill, under a levesel. Chaucer.
The quality of not being able to conduct or transmit; failureto conduct.
The division of a shield palewise, or by a vertical line, esp.for the purpose of putting side by side the arms of husband and wife.See Impale, 3.
